{"word":"ὑπόπτερος","slug":"ὑπόπτερος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑπόπτερος</b></el> <el>(ὑπό-πτερος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πτερόν'><el>πτερόν</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>winged</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; of a ship, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>swift-flying, soaring</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>; <el>ὑπ. φροντίς</el> <i>flighty, giddy</i> thought, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}